oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Framed photograph of William and Alfred Crenshaw and brothers
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: This black and white photograph shows the four sons in the Crenshaw family during childhood. William and Alfred, who were twins, are in the back. On the front left is Thomas DeBow, who died before World War I and the brother in the front middle, Oliver Garland, stayed home during the war to care for their mother, Mary DeBow Crenshaw. The photograph is framed and identifies the children on the back.
